(83, 5, 'story', 'Match each time period with its stage in the story of ''omit'', then arrange them in order:', '{"turns":["He was born from the Latin root meaning ''to send away.'' Built from parts meaning ''away'' and ''to send,'' he was the force that made things disappear, that removed what was no longer needed, that bound absence to presence.","In the age of spiritual discipline, he became the art of selective memory. He was the force that shaped history by what was left out, that bound the remembered to the forgotten, that made the absent seem present.","When minds began to seek truth, he followed knowledge instead of memory. He became the force that shaped understanding by what was excluded, that bound the said to the unsaid, that made the absent seem essential.","In the age of efficiency, he found new work streamlining processes. He was the force that made systems work by removing steps, that bound the necessary to the unnecessary, that made the absent seem productive.","Now he lives in the realm of infinite information, filtering content, curating experience, the ancient force of exclusion finding new forms in the age of abundance."],"settings":["Rome","Medieval Church","Renaissance Humanism","Industrial Age","Digital Age"],"time_periods":["1st c. CE","12th c.","16th c.","19th c.","21st c."]}'::jsonb, '["1st c. CE — Rome → He was born from the Latin root meaning 'to send away.' Built from parts meaning 'away' and 'to send,' he was the force that made things disappear, that removed what was no longer needed, that bound absence to presence.","12th c. — Medieval Church → In the age of spiritual discipline, he became the art of selective memory. He was the force that shaped history by what was left out, that bound the remembered to the forgotten, that made the absent seem present.","16th c. — Renaissance Humanism → When minds began to seek truth, he followed knowledge instead of memory. He became the force that shaped understanding by what was excluded, that bound the said to the unsaid, that made the absent seem essential.","19th c. — Industrial Age → In the age of efficiency, he found new work streamlining processes. He was the force that made systems work by removing steps, that bound the necessary to the unnecessary, that made the absent seem productive.","21st c. — Digital Age → Now he lives in the realm of infinite information, filtering content, curating experience, the ancient force of exclusion finding new forms in the age of abundance."]', '{"feedback":{"fail":"Some centuries landed out of time.","hint":"Trace how absence becomes its own kind of presence.","success":"The centuries fall into place—the word lives again."},"allow_partial_credit":true,"shuffle_each_attempt":true}'::jsonb, 25, 'Wed Oct 22 2025 20:04:12 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)', 'Wed Oct 22 2025 20:04:12 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)') ON CONFLICT (word_id, level) DO NOTHING;
